                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>\n                <date>Feby 13<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1834</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee>,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have postponed writing to you, <sic>untill</sic>\n                <persName>Mr Block</persName><lb/> went on, but as it is now a matter of doubt\n                whether he will<lb/> go at all, I will not longer delay altho' I can with\n                difficulty<lb/> hold my pen as I have a very sore finger—indeed my dear<lb/> fellow,\n                I am very much at a loss for a subject, for sentimental<lb/> letters I write more,\n                local matter would be uninteresting<lb/> &amp; Political I do not understand, yet I\n                could manage to <add>?</add><lb/> your attention for a few minutes I suppose could I\n                bring<lb/> myself once more to like letter writing, but really after<lb/> having\n                written three letters, one to <persName>Aunt Leixa<add>?</add></persName>\n                <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> to <persName>Mrs Spotswood</persName> &amp;\n                    <persName>Miss Ettings</persName>, I am <sic>hartily</sic> tired of<lb/> the\n                business; however to begin something we have received<lb/> your Books, and I am very\n                much pleased with it,<lb/> I am almost ashamed to confess that I did not get<lb/>\n                through with the first copy sent as I found much<lb/> difficulty in\n                    <sic>peacing</sic> them together and the children<lb/> would bother and pull\n                them about so that I got<lb/> impatient and awaited its arrival in a more<lb/>\n                tangible form, and I do request you not to trouble<lb/> yourself to send me <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">your next</hi> production <sic>untill</sic> it<lb/> is\n                completed for it would be useless trouble, as I<lb/> can read so little at the time,\n                I wish to find the peace</p>\n            "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32z1391d/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
