                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p>at which I last left off with the greatest case, I have<lb/> mentioned you &amp; your\n                work to <persName>Mrs Spotswood</persName>, and I presume<lb/> she would like to\n                procure a copy I should be pleased were<lb/> it to get in such able hands, I do not\n                know the number<lb/> of copies sold, <persName>Mr B.</persName> will write you of\n                them when dispo<lb/>sed of, the Jews here are like they are elsewhere rather<lb/>\n                read any thing, understand any thing sooner than their<lb/> religion. I hear\n                    <persName>Seixas Nathan</persName>, is broke for a million<lb/> of Dollars, is\n                it really true? <sic>let</sic> me know when you<lb/> next write all you know of the\n                matter—what<lb/> was the <sic>occation</sic> of <persName>Miss Cohen's</persName>\n                death do you know?<lb/> I was very much shocked to hear it—are you better<lb/> I\n                heard you had been sick, I think <persName>Isaac</persName> a<lb/> trip this way\n                would be of service to you the sight of<lb/> old friends better than medicine\n                suppose you try<lb/> it and let me have the pleasure of seeing you soon<lb/> I have\n                a room at your disposal, and you could<lb/> be as much retired when you wish as you\n                    <add>?</add><lb/> indeed I'm sure <sic>travelling</sic> over the mountains<lb/>\n                would be of great service to you and I should be<lb/> delighted to see you at my\n                house—your old friend<lb/>\n                <persName>Eleanor</persName> is quite well, her husband is with you before this<lb/>\n                <persName>Mrs Marks</persName> a family are also well and desire<lb/>\n                remembrance—Present me to all <sic>enquiring</sic> friends</p>\n            "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32z1391d/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
